Monday August 19th 2013 3:47 pm -04:00,Issues related to spacing uppercase lowercase and all that are known as Coding Style. Theres no master rule or suggestion on how to do things but in Python the so-called authoritative document which provides guidance is known as PEP 8 which stands for Python Enhancement Proposal number 8:http://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008/So the rule of thumb is that you should have a space before and after an operator i.e. before and after the +. Except in certain circumstances i.e. when grouping operators with different orders of precedence and so on. Theres a lot of good examples in PEP 8 of what not to do as well. Yes:i = i + 1submitted += 1x = x*2 - 1hypot2 = x*x + y*yc = (a+b) * (a-b)No:i=i+1submitted +=1x = x * 2 - 1hypot2 = x * x + y * yc = (a + b) * (a - b), Resolved,15
