Friday September 6th 2013 10:08 am -04:00,Theres a couple of things going on...First this is known as lazy evaluation. Which means that depending on the variables and the operator Python may only evaluate the first value and stop. Or it may be continue to the end.Second all values that are non-zero etc. are interpreted as True i.e. both cents and dollars are considered as True since theyre not zero etc.So if you use the AND operator it will keep evaluating all the values until the end and only return the last one. If you were to use the OR operator for example then Python would stop at cents since its True and would not need to check anything else.Some code in action...  >>> dollars = 18>>> cents = 53>>> pesos = 0>>> cents and dollars18>>> cents or dollars53>>> cents and pesos and dollars0>>> cents or pesos or dollars53>>> pesos or cents or dollars53, Resolved,2
