Wednesday October 2nd 2013 5:58 am -04:00,Yes its possible. But it all depends on your ISP (Internet Service Provider).Some ISPs allow you to purchase a static IP address from them. Or you may already have a static IP address and its just a matter of routing incoming traffic to the port where your web server is located.Big word of caution though not all ISPs allow their subscribers to host a web server. Some even block certain ports and it may even be a violation of your agreement to host a web server.Edit: You can also use a dynamic IP address as well. But again that might violate your agreement.  ,None,0
