Wednesday October 2nd 2013 11:29 am -04:00,New IDs dont get created simply because of new values or new lists. For example if the integer 6 already exists then a new ID wont be created. What happens instead is one two or three different items will simply all point to the same location.Whats more important in this question is to follow whats happening with i. Youll notice that in the for loop it gets assigned the values of 0 3 6 due to the step parameter of 3.So plug in those values for i and then look at the corresponding indexes and their values to see whats being added up. And subsequently put into the merged list.  Edit: Short answer no new ID for 6 because it already existed. New ID14 because integer 15 didnt exist.  , Unresolved,0
